<P ALIGN="CENTER"><FONT SIZE="-1" COLOR="GREEN"><I>Rig Veda</I>, tr. by Ralph T.H. Griffith, [1896], at sacred-texts.com</FONT></P><HR></p>  <h3 align="center" align="center">HYMN CLVIII. S&#363;rya.</h3>  
<p>1. MAY S&#363;rya guard us out of heaven, and V&#257;ta from the firmament,<br> And Agni from terrestrial spots.<br> 2 Thou Savitar whose flame deserves hundred libations, be thou pleased:<br> From failing lightning keep us safe.<br> 3 May Savitar the God, and may Parvata also give us sight;<br> May the Creator give us sight.<br> 4 Give sight unto our eye, give thou our bodies sight that they may see:<br> May we survey, discern this world.<br> 5 Thus, S&#363;rya, may we look on thee, on thee most lovely to behold,<br> See clearly with the eyes of men.</p>  
